Eggdrop News
============

Major and incompatible changes by release. Full changelog in
doc/Changes1.10. See UPGRADING for migration help.

Back up your config and userfile before upgrading.


devinkbrown fork (based on v1.10.1)
------------------------------------

Wave 81 — CSPRNG, string safety, expanded test suite

  Security — CSPRNG:
    - random()/srandom() replaced with getrandom(2) (Linux) or
      arc4random_buf (BSD/macOS) across the entire codebase.
    - randint() is now a static inline using CSPRNG, eliminating
      predictable random in password generation, blowfish IV, and
      DNS query IDs.
    - Removed init_random() from main.c.
    - Blowfish IV generation uses getrandom(2).
    - Python rand() routes through the CSPRNG randint().

  String safety — complete:
    - egg_atoi(): safe strtol wrapper replacing all 202 raw atoi()
      calls across 46 files.
    - my_strcpy() sites converted to stpcpy() in misc.c and irc.mod.
      my_strcpy() retained for ABI compatibility (slot 91).
    - malloc_strcpy macro (filedb3.h) optimised to use memcpy.
    - Unbounded sscanf %s in language.c fixed with %255s.
    - Zero remaining: strcpy, sprintf, strcat, strncpy, strncat,
      strtok, gets, system(), raw atoi, unbounded sscanf %s.

  Test suite:
    - test_match: 8 → 22 tests (CIDR, cron_match, addr_match)
    - test_flags: 10 → 56 tests (sanity_check, break_down_flags,
      flagrec_eq)
    - test_misc: rewritten, 18 tests (newsplit, rmspace, splitnick)
    - test_net: rewritten, 8 tests (iptostr IPv4/IPv6)
    - 7 executables, all passing under ASAN+UBSAN, zero warnings.

Wave 80 — LMDB storage, buffer elimination, strlcpy migration

  Pluggable storage backend (egg_store):
    - vtable-based architecture: open/close/load/save/export/import
    - Flat-file backend: thin wrapper, full backward compatibility
    - LMDB backend: crash-safe, auto-recovery from crashed userfiles.
      Two-layer design — blob for crash recovery, structured
      sub-databases (users, hosts, accounts, ignores) for lookups.
    - Config: [storage] backend = "lmdb" or "flat"

  strlcpy/strlcat → op_strbuf_t migration:
    - 677 call sites audited, 127 (19%) converted to op_strbuf_t
    - Global OBUF[1024] in botmsg.c eliminated
    - DCC display callbacks changed to op_strbuf_t *

  Buffer elimination:
    - server.c: CAP word-wrap output via op_strbuf_steal()
    - dccutil.c/userent.c: fixed-size buffers → op_strbuf_t

  Dead code removal:
    - Pre-1.3.0 botnet protocol (NO_OLD_BOTNET) stripped

Wave 77 — Python API 100% parity (239 commands)

  65 new Python commands, total 239/239:
    - Botnet (9), User database (8), DCC/Partyline (7),
      Channel management (7), Ban/Exempt/Invite (6), Ignore (4),
      Timer (4), Server (3), Misc (17)

Wave 76 — Python API expansion, linebuf port, tclhash unification

  Python API: 26 new commands (174/197, 88% parity)
  Python auto-source: TOML [scripts] auto-detects .py files
  linebuf port: char *inbuf → op_linebuf (slab-allocated, CRLF-aware)
  tclhash: unified init_bind(), fixed missing tables in no-Tcl builds

Wave 75 — Tcl decoupling, zero-warning build

  Tcl decoupling:
    - All #ifdef HAVE_TCL removed from application source (58 files)
    - 12 new lush.h stubs for no-op Tcl replacements
    - 19 irreducible HAVE_TCL markers remain (lush.h, tcl.c, tclegg.h,
      tclhash.c)
    - notcl_setvar/notcl_getvar available in both configurations

  Python API: 33 new commands (timers, user/module, DCC, misc)

  Zero-warning build: ~80 warnings eliminated across 20+ files

  Feature improvements:
    - .status shows scripting engines, module count, RSS memory
    - .set works in non-Tcl builds
    - .python partyline command

C23 modernisation

  - Entire codebase compiled as -std=gnu23 with -Wshadow=local
  - Variables declared at first use, constexpr, bool, for-init
  - op_strbuf_t wired through all string-construction sites
  - const correctness propagated across function signatures
  - libop synced: CIDR parsing helpers, C11 thread pool

Python API (earlier waves)

  43 commands: channel presence, modes/actions, ban/exempt/invite
  management, user channel records, eggtools.py utility library

Tcl optional — no-Tcl builds are complete

  - All TOML config keys reach their C variables
  - Server persistence via old_add_server (server_table[55])
  - Python registers as sole scripting engine automatically
  - Variable registry via notcl_setvar/notcl_getvar

Build system

  - Meson + Ninja replaces autoconf/make
  - LTO enabled by default, -fno-strict-aliasing, -Wl,--as-needed
  - -fvisibility=hidden for module .so files
  - Native CPU tuning via -Dnative-opt (off by default)

Platform support

  - macOS/BSD: kqueue backend
  - Windows native: IOCP backend via libop
  - Cygwin: plain POSIX path (select)
  - I/O priority: io_uring → epoll → kqueue → IOCP → select

IRC protocol

  - IRCX/Ophion: CREATE, PROP, ACCESS, +q owner mode
  - Async DNS resolver (non-blocking UDP)
  - DNS-over-TLS (DoT, RFC 7858)
  - allow_hello, allow_addhost config settings

Configuration

  - TOML format: eggdrop.toml, eggdrop-basic.toml
  - Interactive wizard: eggdrop --setup
  - Full TOML↔Tcl setting parity (128+ settings)
  - Per-channel [[chanset]] blocks
  - Inline Tcl: [tcl] code = """..."""
  - Auto-create userfile when owner is set

Performance

  - libop allocation (op_malloc/op_free) for all 750+ sites
  - O(1) Robin Hood hash tables for binds, members, masks
  - Slab allocator for memberlist and masklist nodes
  - Twitch: fixed-size buffers → dynamic allocation

Bug fixes

  - [paths] ordering: module-registered variables no longer dropped
  - [paths] lang_dir support
  - io_uring SQPOLL: 3 bugs preventing IRC registration fixed
  - webui: snprintf using sizeof(char*) instead of buffer length
  - Various memory, type, and const-correctness fixes

Documentation

  - All documentation overhauled with modern formatting
  - INSTALL rewritten for Meson with per-platform instructions
  - README with full fork rationale, feature summary, quick start
  - FEATURES with complete capability listing
  - DESIGN.md: architecture, internals, data structures, test suite
  - COMPILE-GUIDE: build troubleshooting FAQ


Eggdrop v1.10.1 (upstream)
----------------------------

  - kqueue I/O backend for macOS/BSD
  - SCRAM SASL authentication
  - TLS handshake completion check for botnet linking
  - CHANSET bind for channel setting changes
  - Python module crash fixes, owner flag requirement
  - PBKDF2 build fix for NetBSD
  - Various crash, timing, and TLS fixes


Eggdrop v1.10.0 (upstream)
----------------------------

  - Autoscripts: view/download/install Tcl scripts from partyline
  - Account-based user identification
  - IRCv3: userhost-in-names, standard-replies
  - Python module with embedded interpreter
  - Tcl 9 compatibility
  - CHGHOST bind, hidden-host and got-chanlist events
  - TLS required by default
  - Language files converted to UTF-8
  - copy-to-tmp and quick-logs options removed


